# Email OTP Verification + Google Auth Improvements

## Problem

1. **No email verification** — anyone can register with a fake email, no proof of ownership
2. **Google OAuth ignores role** — always creates users as [student](file:///c:/Users/mukun/Downloads/staysafe/Backend/src/controllers/bookingController.js#528-590), no role selector
3. **RegisterPage has no Google button** — only LoginPage has "Sign in with Google"

## Proposed Flow

### Email/Password Registration (2-step)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant F as Frontend
    participant B as Backend
    participant E as Email

    U->>F: Fill name, email, password, role
    F->>B: POST /auth/register (pending user)
    B->>E: Send 6-digit OTP email
    B-->>F: { pendingUserId, message }
    F->>F: Show OTP input screen
    U->>F: Enter OTP
    F->>B: POST /auth/verify-otp { pendingUserId, otp }
    B->>B: Create real User, mark emailVerified
    B-->>F: { token, user } (auto-login)
```

### Google OAuth with Role Selection

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant F as Frontend (RegisterPage)
    participant B as Backend

    U->>F: Select role, click "Sign up with Google"
    F->>B: GET /auth/google?role=owner
    B->>B: Passport OAuth → Google consent
    B->>B: Create/find user with selected role
    B-->>F: Redirect with token
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Google-authenticated emails are inherently verified by Google, so **no OTP step** is needed for Google sign-ups.

---

## Proposed Changes

### Backend

---

#### [NEW] `src/models/PendingUser.js`

Temporary model for unverified registrations with TTL auto-cleanup:

| Field | Type | Notes |
|-------|------|-------|
| [name](file:///c:/Users/mukun/Downloads/staysafe/Backend/src/routes/documentRoutes.js#20-25) | String | From registration form |
| `email` | String | unique, indexed |
| `passwordHash` | String | Pre-hashed |
| `role` | String | student/owner/admin |
| `otp` | String | 6-digit, hashed with bcrypt |
| `otpExpiresAt` | Date | 10 minutes TTL |
| `attempts` | Number | Max 5 attempts, prevents brute-force |
| `createdAt` | Date | TTL index: auto-delete after 1 hour |

> [!TIP]
> Using a separate model (not the User model) keeps the main User collection clean — unverified registrations automatically expire and get deleted by MongoDB TTL.

---

#### [NEW] `src/services/authService.js`

DRY service consolidating auth business logic:

| Function | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `createPendingUser(data)` | Hash password + OTP, create PendingUser, send OTP email |
| `verifyOtp(pendingUserId, otp)` | Validate OTP, create real User, generate JWT, cleanup |
| `resendOtp(pendingUserId)` | Generate new OTP, reset attempts, send email |
| `generateOtp()` | 6-digit random number (shared helper) |
| `issueToken(user)` | JWT sign with `AUTH.JWT_EXPIRES_IN` (DRY — used by register, login, Google) |

---

#### [MODIFY] [src/routes/authRoutes.js](file:///c:/Users/mukun/Downloads/staysafe/Backend/src/routes/authRoutes.js)

| Change | Details |
|--------|---------|
| `POST /register` | Now creates `PendingUser` + sends OTP, does NOT create real User yet |
| `POST /verify-otp` | **New** — validates OTP, creates User, returns JWT |
| `POST /resend-otp` | **New** — resends OTP to pending user |
| `POST /login` | Add `emailVerified` check — reject unverified users |
| `GET /google` | Accept `?role=` query param, pass to strategy via `state` |
| Google callback | Read role from state, use it when creating new user |

---

#### [MODIFY] [src/models/User.js](file:///c:/Users/mukun/Downloads/staysafe/Backend/src/models/User.js)

Add one field:

```diff
+ emailVerified: { type: Boolean, default: false },
```

Google users get `emailVerified: true` automatically. Existing users get `emailVerified: true` via a migration-safe default.

